Zhiqiang,

I use Eclipse 3.3 and Sun JRE 1.6.0.

Steps to reproduce:

1. Open eclipse with BIRT framework installed.
2. Create new report or open existent.
3. In layout tab of editor click on the paragraph mark on the ruler (see attachment "Paragraph mark on the ruler").
4. Press Delete button on the keybord.

Eclipse do not show this NPE, you can see it only in Error Log view (see attachment "NPE in Error Log view").

I found problem in code.
Class: org.eclipse.birt.report.designer.internal.ui.command.WrapperCommandStack
Method: execute

public void execute( Command command )
	{
		ar.startTrans( command.getLabel() );
		command.execute( );
		ar.commit( );

	}

In described case command == null and in first line of this method NPE will occur.
